The Social Cluster will detail its plans during the 21-day national lockdown. Several other briefings will be held today as well. There are now 554 cases of Covid-19 across the country. JOHANNESBURG - An Inter-Ministerial Committee dealing with coronavirus in South Africa will address the nation on Tuesday. The Social Cluster is expected to detail its plans during the 21-day national lockdown announced by President Cyril Ramaphosa's in his address on Monday evening. COVID-19: 21-days lockdown explained South Africa will be on lockdown from Thursday evening. There are now 554 cases of COVID-19 across the country. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.